# NestJS — Project Conventions

This is the **NestJS 10** backend in the Tripteki parallel-codebase family. It shares the same domain model, API contract, and event names with FastAPI and Laravel siblings.

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | NestJS 10 + TypeScript (strict, SWC builder) |
| Runtime | **Bun** (`bun run`); README may still reference npm |
| ORM | Prisma — PostgreSQL (migrations) + MongoDB (`db push`) |
| Cache/Queue | Redis — cache, Bull job queues |
| REST | Swagger at `/api/docs` |
| GraphQL | Apollo at `/graphql` |
| WebSockets | Socket.IO — room-based emits to `user.{id}` |
| Auth | JWT — access + refresh tokens |
| Mail | Handlebars templates via Nest mailer |
| i18n | nest-i18n |
| Scheduler | `@nestjs/schedule` |

## Directory layout

```
src/
  app/                          # Infrastructure layer
    configs/                    # registerAs config modules
    providers/                  # Boot providers (AppHttpProvider, etc.)
    drivers/                    # External service drivers
    databases/                  # Prisma clients
    helpers/                    # Shared utilities
    langs/                      # i18n files
  v1/
    api/{domain}/               # REST domain modules
      controllers/
      services/
      repositories/
      dtos/                     # validator, transformer, enum
      events/
      listeners/
      processors/               # Bull queue processors
      middlewares/
      modules/
      databases/
      views/                    # Email templates
    graphql/{domain}/           # Parallel GraphQL stack
      resolvers/
      services/
      dtos/
      middlewares/
      modules/
test/                           # E2E tests only (*.e2e-spec.ts)
  test.case.ts                  # setupTestApp, setupAuthTestApp
storage/logs/
public/
```

## Naming conventions

| Artifact | Convention | Example |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| File | dot-separated lowercase | `user.auth.service.ts` |
| Class | PascalCase | `UserAuthService` |
| Event | PascalCase + Event suffix | `UserAuthLoggedInEvent` |
| Validator DTO | `*.validator.dto.ts` | `user.validator.dto.ts` |
| Transformer DTO | `*.transformer.dto.ts` | `user.transformer.dto.ts` |
| Enum | `*.enum.ts` | `user-role.enum.ts` |
| Import path | Absolute from `src/` | `import { X } from 'src/app/...'` |

No `@` path alias in tsconfig — always use `src/...` imports.

## Shared API contract (all backends)

### Endpoints
- REST base: `/api/v1`
- Swagger docs: `/api/docs`
- GraphQL: `/graphql`
- Health/status: `/api/status`

### Auth
- `POST /api/v1/auth/login` — returns `{ access_token, refresh_token, token_type, expires_in }`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/refresh` — accepts `{ refresh_token }` or cookie
- `POST /api/v1/auth/register`, `POST /api/v1/auth/logout`
- `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` — returns user profile
- Login supports `remember` flag for extended refresh token

### Error responses
```json
// Validation (HTTP 422)
{ "detail": [{ "loc": ["body", "email"], "msg": "...", "type": "..." }] }

// General (HTTP 4xx/5xx)
{ "message": "Human-readable error" }
```

### Pagination
```json
{
  "data": [...],
  "meta": { "total": 100, "per_page": 15, "current_page": 1, "last_page": 7 },
  "links": { "first": "...", "last": "...", "prev": null, "next": "..." }
}
```

### Rate limiting
- Throttle/rate-limit applies in **production only** (`NODE_ENV=production`)
- Do not throttle in development or tests

## Environment variables

```
APP_NAME, APP_SECRET, APP_PORT, APP_ENV, APP_LOCALE, APP_TIMEZONE
FRONTEND_URL
NODE_ENV
MEMORY_REDIS_HOST, MEMORY_REDIS_PORT, MEMORY_REDIS_PASSWORD
DATABASE_POSTGRE_URI, DATABASE_MONGO_URI
MAIL_URI
SWAGGER_TITLE, SWAGGER_DESCRIPTION, SWAGGER_VERSION
```

Config loaded via `@nestjs/config` `registerAs()` in `src/app/configs/`.

## Setup commands

```bash
bun install
bun run prisma              # Generate Prisma clients
bun run postgre:migrate     # PostgreSQL migrations
bun run mongo:migrate       # MongoDB schema push
bun run dev                 # Start dev server
bun run build               # Production build
```

## Testing

```bash
bun test                    # Jest e2e watch mode
bun run test:e2e            # Jest e2e with coverage
```

- **E2E only** — no unit test suite; do not add unit tests unless requested
- **Requires Redis** running at `127.0.0.1:6379` for e2e tests
- Default test user: `user@mail.com` / `12345678`
- Helpers: `setupTestApp()`, `setupAuthTestApp()` in `test/test.case.ts`

## Lint

```bash
bun run lint    # Prettier + ESLint (@tripteki/eslint-config, @tripteki/prettier-config)
```
